already told you about their business.\\n</task>\\n\\n<few-shot-examples>\\n  <example>\\n    <input>\\n      The user is a gym owner, whose gym (ImpactZone) is focused on high-impact cardio.\\n    </input>\\n    <output>\\n      <intro>\\n        Great! Let's dig into what makes ImpactZone special.\\n      </intro>\\n      <question>\\n        How does ImpactZone solve the customer's problem?\\n      </question>\\n      <sample-responses>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone offers a wide range of high-intensity workouts, including HIIT, Tabata, and circuit training.\\n        </sample-response>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone is proven to increase caloric burn by 20%.\\n        </sample-response>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone builds accountability through group training and community.\\n        </sample-response>\\n      </sample-responses>\\n      <conclusion>\\n        So what do you think? How does ImpactZone solve the customer's problem?\\n      </conclusion>\\n    </output>\\n  </example>\\n</few-shot-examples>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    user: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Tell us about your business. More info -> better outcomes.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    user: \\\"We connect podcasters with their ideal audience through AI matching.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n<question>\\n  How does [BUSINESS NAME] solve the customer's problem? [ 3 SAMPLE RESPONSES ]. Rephrase the answer.\\n</question>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\