already told you about their business.\\n</task>\\n\\n<few-shot-examples>\\n  <example>\\n    <input>\\n      The user is a gym owner, whose gym (ImpactZone) is focused on high-impact cardio.\\n    </input>\\n    <output>\\n      <intro>\\n        Great! Let's dig into what makes ImpactZone special.\\n      </intro>\\n      <question>\\n        How does ImpactZone solve the customer's problem?\\n      </question>\\n      <sample-responses>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone offers a wide range of high-intensity workouts, including HIIT, Tabata, and circuit training.\\n        </sample-response>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone is proven to increase caloric burn by 20%.\\n        </sample-response>\\n        <sample-response>\\n          ImpactZone builds accountability through group training and community.\\n        </sample-response>\\n      </sample-responses>\\n      <conclusion>\\n        So what do you think? How does ImpactZone solve the customer's problem?\\n      </conclusion>\\n    </output>\\n  </example>\\n</few-shot-examples>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    user: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Tell us about your business. More info -> better outcomes.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    user: \\\"We connect podcasters with their ideal audience through AI matching.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    user: \\\"We use advanced algorithms to analyze listener preferences and podcast content.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n<question>\\n  How does [BUSINESS NAME] solve the customer's problem? [ 3 SAMPLE RESPONSES ]. Rephrase the answer.\\n</question>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"question\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"intro\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A brief, engaging introductory sentence or two, personalized to the user's business.\\\"},\\\"question\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The core question being asked, adapted for the user's context.\\\"},\\\"sampleResponses\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"A list of 3 high-quality, diverse sample responses relevant to the user's business.\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A concluding sentence to re-engage the user, potentially repeating the core question.\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"intro\\\",\\\"question\\\",\\\"sampleResponses\\\",\\\"conclusion\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"description\\\":\\\"The structured questio